# Definitions

Version Control Systems : They are a category of tools that help a software team manage changes to the source code over time.
It keeps track of every modification to the code in a special kind of database.
VCS are sometimes known as SCM(Source Code Management) or RCS(Revision Control System).

GIT : It is the most widely used  Distributed VCS.

GIT Repository : It is a virtual storage of the project. It allows us to save versions of our code which we can access when needed.
